An API (Application Programming Interface) is a way for two applications to communicate with each other.

It allows one program to send a request and another program to return data or perform an action.

Simple Example:
When a frontend app sends a request to a backend server:
    Frontend → API → Backend → Database

Example:
A React app sends a request to get users.

The Flask API receives the request.

The API fetches data from the database.

The API sends the response back to the frontend.

Example API Request
curl http://localhost:5000/users

The API returns data like:

[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Gaurav",
    "email": "gaurav@example.com"
  }
]


Common API Methods

| Method | Purpose         |
| ------ | --------------- |
| GET    | Retrieve data   |
| POST   | Create new data |
| PUT    | Update data     |
| DELETE | Remove data     |
